            <h2>About</h2>
            <p>
            The Wildlife Conservation Society (WCS) is a global leader in conservation, dedicated to saving wildlife and wild
            places. WCS operates in more than 55 countries and has over 3,500 staff, with a focus on protecting areas with high
            ecological integrity. The organization's mission includes species protection, habitat preservation, scientific research,
            and community-driven conservation strategies. WCS aims to create a future where humans coexist harmoniously with
            wildlife and their habitats, emphasizing mutual respect and understanding.</p>
